{
  "message": "docs(proposals): leaf-extraction README \u2014 pause point for ft-t2d70 children (ft-g6sa8/otfxs/0pykm)\n\nFiled 3 child beads under ft-t2d70 (.1 error-types, .2 config-types,\n.3 policy-types). Claimed ft-g6sa8 (.1) and inspected error.rs before\nstarting moves.\n\nDiscovery: parent ADR's \"117 LOC\" estimate was wrong. error.rs is\n1486 lines and the load-bearing enums (Error, StorageError,\nWeztermError) carry 16 references to crate::network_reliability inside\ninherent-impl method bodies. Rust's orphan rule for inherent impls\nblocks splitting the type from its impls, so a clean leaf extract\nrequires either a sub-leaf for network_reliability OR a refactor of\nError::error_kind into a free function.\n\nPausing per the user's \"OR file all 3 children + a README and pause for\nreview\" branch. README enumerates three options (\u03b1 leaf-clean subset\nonly / \u03b2 error_kind refactor + full extract / \u03b3 re-estimate and defer)\nand recommends \u03b2.\n\nSame discovery is likely for the other two children \u2014 config.rs and\npolicy.rs are both entangled with connector + mcp types per the parent\nADR's reverse-dep survey.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
